Your `setInterval` time isn&#39;t decreasing, it isn&#39;t stopping. You&#39;ve never told it to stop, so what&#39;s most likely happening is that you&#39;re duplicating the `setInterval`s each time you call the function, meaning that multiples are running at once time. This would give you the false impression that your current click, causes a reaction, sooner. When in fact, it was a previous `setInterval`, executing. 

If you only want it to happen once, say `onclick`, then use `setTimeout` instead.

